{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_17","type":"agent_message","text":"The first coarse probe exposed an important complication: identical-looking coordinate clicks may be coupled to hidden turn progression, because the square sometimes advances downward while the basket remains fixed. I’m separating coordinate effect from turn effect by repeating the same click on independent clones and then replaying short same-click sequences. The square-and-basket geometry gives a useful dense metric: vertical distance between their centers."}}
